Overview

We will learn today

  • Numerai prediction challenge
  • h2o machine learning and modeling framework
  • Model building with R
  • Evaluating prediction models

About Numerai

  • Data science tournament to predict stock market
  • Financial data is obfuscated
  • Good prediction models are awarded prizes
    • Prize = NMR cryptocurrency
    • Amount is based on how much staked

Goal of Numerai

  • Founded by Richard Craib in 2015
  • Build the world's last hedge fund
  • Combination of many models to predict
  • Democratizes access to stock market wealth
  • More in this blog post and this short film

Numerai Data

  • Very large for R
    • typically 350K+ observations and 300+ columns
  • Fortunately data is cleaned and standardized
  • Features are all numeric
  • Downloadable as simple CSV flatfiles
  • API makes it easy to download and upload predictions

Getting Numerai Data with R

  • Package Rnumerai makes API simple for R
  • Need a Numerai account to get public id and api key
  • Still have the challenge with big data
  • The modeling framework h2o is a useful tool
    • https://www.h2o.ai/

Download Numerai Data

library(Rnumerai)

set_public_id("<-- your account public id -->")
set_api_key("<-- your accout api key -->")

account_info()


dataDir <- "./numerai_datasets"

download_data(dataDir)

h2o Overview

  • Goal is to “democratize AI for everyone”
  • Framework for buidling models on large data
    • Data flow and cleaning
    • Model work flow
    • Cluster multiple computers for high performance
    • Work seamless with R

Start h2o Cluster

library(h2o)

#### initiate h2o
h2o.init("localhost", nthreads = -1, max_mem_size = "8g")

Import Numerai Data

### import data to h2o
pathToTrain <- "./numerai_datasets/numerai_training_data.csv"
pathToTest <- "./numerai_datasets/numerai_tournament_data.csv"
train.hex <- h2o.importFile(path = pathToTrain)

Setup Model Attributes

##### model variable names
modelvars <- names(train.hex)[grep("feature", names(train.hex))]

##### target variable name
targetvar <- "target"

### model training parameters
SEEDVAL <- 12345

Split Data for Evaluation

#### split into devel and valid sets
train.split <- h2o.splitFrame(data = train.hex, ratios=0.75,seed = SEEDVAL)
train.dev <- train.split[[1]]
train.val <- train.split[[2]]

nrow(train.dev)

[1] 376519

nrow(train.val)

[1] 125289

Fit A Model

Gradient Boosted Machine model

fitGBM <- h2o.gbm(x=modelvars, y=targetvar, training_frame = train.dev
                  , ntrees = 30
                  , min_rows = 100
                  , learn_rate = 0.05
                  , distribution = "AUTO")

Predictions to data.frame object

### convert to data.frame format
modelpred.dev <- as.data.frame(pred.gbm.dev)
modelpred.val <- as.data.frame(pred.gbm.val)

### add target variable
modelpred.dev$target <- as.numeric(as.vector(train.dev[[targetvar]]))
modelpred.val$target <- as.numeric(as.vector(train.val[[targetvar]]))

Model Evaluation

perf.gbm.dev <- h2o.performance(model = fitGBM, newdata=train.dev)
perf.gbm.val <- h2o.performance(model = fitGBM, newdata=train.val)

h2o.rmse(perf.gbm.dev)

[1] 0.2228911

h2o.rmse(perf.gbm.val)

[1] 0.2227899

Evaluate Development Split for Numerai

correlation across eras

### convert to vector
eraindex <- as.vector(train.dev[["era"]])
eras <- unique(eraindex)

eracorr <- lapply(eras, function(i) cor(modelpred.dev[eraindex==i,c("target","predict")], method="spearman")[2,1] )
names(eracorr) <- eras

eramean.dev <- mean(unlist(eracorr))
erasd.dev <- sd(unlist(eracorr))
erasharpe.dev <- eramean.dev/erasd.dev

Evaluate Validation Split for Numerai

eraindex <- as.vector(train.val[["era"]])
eras <- unique(eraindex)

eracorr <- lapply(eras, function(i) cor(modelpred.val[eraindex==i,c("target","predict")], method="spearman")[2,1] )
names(eracorr) <- eras

eramean.val <- mean(unlist(eracorr))
erasd.val <- sd(unlist(eracorr))
erasharpe.val <- eramean.dev/erasd.dev

Show Era Performance

data.frame(type=c("DEVEL","VALID")
  ,eramean=c(eramean.dev, eramean.val)
  ,erasharpe=c(erasharpe.dev,erasharpe.val)
)

   type    eramean erasharpe
1 DEVEL 0.09559195  2.781491
2 VALID 0.04501413  2.781491

Plot Era Correlations

barplot(unlist(eracorr), main="correlation to target")
abline(h=0.002, col="blue", lty=2)
grid()

Submission File for Numerai

###### score tournament file ######
pred.gbm.tourn <- h2o.predict(fitGBM, newdata=tournament.hex)

pred <- data.frame(id=as.vector(tournament.hex[["id"]]), prediction=as.vector(pred.gbm.tourn[["predict"]]) )

# Save the predictions out to a CSV file
write.csv(pred, file="submission.csv", quote=F, row.names=F)

Tips for Improving Performance

  • Look at different modeling methods
    • Random Forest, Linear Regression, Neural Net
    • Dimension reduction like principal components
  • Validation methods
    • Different ways to split by era
    • Cross validation
  • Numarai support
    • Forum and Chat
  • Look at other prediction challenges
    • Kaggle, KDNuggets
